        <mxCell id="FzBO6bfzB8ek5okat1Op-2" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;fontSize=14;" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;JSON stands for JavaScript Object Notation.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;JSON is a plain text data format used to store and send data between applications.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;In JavaScript, JSON is primarily used to exchange data between a web server and a client.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;JSON is similar to the syntax of creating JavaScript objects.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
